<title>UK: UK shares open slightly firmer, gains seen limited.</title>
<headline>UK shares open slightly firmer, gains seen limited.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-04-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>The UK's FTSE 100 opened slightly firmer on Tuesday, but dealers said the upside was limited as concerns about interest rates, the strength of sterling and the upcoming UK election keeps buyers at bay.</p>
<p>The leading blue chip index was up 4.5 points at 4,276.2 at 0740 GMT amid a weaker gilts and FTSE futures.</p>
<p>FTSE 100 advancers narrowly outpaced decliners 49 to 37.</p>
